z_var = []
for col in df.columns:
    var = df[col].var()
    if var == 0:
        z_var.append(col)
        
if z_var:
    print("The columns having zero variance are : " + z_var)
    df.drop(columns = z_var , inplace = True)
    
else :
    print("There are no zero variance columns found...")

In [21]:
 def outlier(col):
    q1,q3 = np.percentile(col,[25,75])
    iqr = q3-q1
    lw = q1-1.5*iqr
    uw = q3+1.5*iqr
    return lw,uw

def correlated_feature_pairs(dataset, threshold):
    correlated_pairs = []
    corr_matrix = dataset.corr()
    
    for i in range(len(corr_matrix.columns)):
        for j in range (i):
            if abs(corr_matrix.iloc[i,j]) > threshold:
                feature1 = corr_matrix.columns[i]
                feature2 = corr_matrix.columns[j]
                correlated_pairs.append((feature1,feature2))
                
    return correlated_pairs

def correlation_removal(dataset, threshold):
    col_corr = set()
    correlated_pairs = []
    corr_matrix = dataset.corr()
    for i in range(len(corr_matrix.columns)):
        for j in range(i):
            if abs(corr_matrix.iloc[i,j]) > threshold:
                colname = corr_matrix.columns[i]
                col_corr.add(colname)
    return col_corr
